parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag deploys inadvertently
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and in some cases, the airbag may not deploy in a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag deploys inadvertently
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clock spring can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, and in some cases, the airbag may not deploy in a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag deploys inadvertently
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause the airbag to deploy with excessive force, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the airbag deploys inadvertently
or the airbag fails to deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil springs can cause the tire to puncture, leading to loss of control and potentially serious accidents.
symptoms: Abnormal noise
clunking or popping sound
vehicle pulling to one side
loss of tire pressure
tire puncture
vehicle becoming unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear coil springs can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control and potentially serious accidents.
symptoms: Abnormal noise
clunking or popping sound
vehicle pulling to one side
loss of tire pressure
tire puncture
vehicle becoming unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe and bushing can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control and potentially serious accidents.
symptoms: Abnormal noise
clunking or popping sound
vehicle pulling to one side
loss of tire pressure
tire puncture
vehicle becoming unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The power steering light comes on
the steering wheel locks or becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel vibrates or makes a clunking noise
the power steering assist fails
and the brakes may also fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column and Adjustment Lever Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and adjustment lever can cause the steering wheel to become loose or difficult to turn, leading to loss of control of the vehicle, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The steering column and adjustment lever are loose
the steering wheel feels loose or vibrates
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the power steering assist may fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Coil Spring and Sway Bar Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the coil spring and sway bar can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The coil spring and sway bar break
the vehicle's steering becomes unstable
the vehicle pulls to one side
and the bumper may fall off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag and seatbelt systems can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbags do not deploy
the seatbelt pre-tensioners do not activate
and the vehicle's speed sensor and intake air temperature sensor may have fault codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and potential injuries.
symptoms: The rack and pinion fails without warning
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and the vehicle pulls to one side.
